author: CBC News
title: What you need to know about COVID-19 in B.C. on April 14, 2020
description: B.C. provincial health officer Dr. Bonnie Henry announced 63 new coronavirus cases in the province on Monday, bringing the total number of identified cases to 1,266.
content:
THE LATEST:
  • Health officials announced 11 more deaths over Saturday and Sunday, bringing B.C.'s total to 69.
  • The total number of people who have tested positive rose by 45 to 1,490.
  • 926 people have recovered from the illness.
